Key Match Events: France won 1-0 against Belgium in the Euro 2024 Round of 16.
Vertonghen scored an own goal in the 85th minute.
Tchouameni, Griezmann, and Rabiot had notable performances.
Vertonghen and Tedesco received yellow cards in the 76th minute.
Mangala received a yellow card in the 90+3 minute.
Pre-Game Insights: France head coach Didier Deschamps faced a selection dilemma in the final third for the match.
Kylian Mbappe returned to the starting lineup after recovering from a broken nose.
Antoine Griezmann was expected to return to the lineup after being benched in the final group game.
Marcus Thuram was reportedly set to start alongside Mbappe.
Deschamps was expected to change the formation to a 4-3-1-2 shape.
France's backline remained unchanged throughout the tournament.
